  "root_text": {
    "sn2.18:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 2.18 ",
    "sn2.18:0.2": "2. Anāthapiṇḍikavagga ",
    "sn2.18:0.3": "Kakudhasutta ",
    "sn2.18:1.1": "Evaṁ me sutaṁ—",
    "sn2.18:1.2": "ekaṁ samayaṁ bhagavā sākete viharati añjanavane migadāye. ",
    "sn2.18:1.3": "Atha kho kakudho devaputto abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṁ añjanavanaṁ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṁ abhivādetvā ekamantaṁ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṁ ṭhito kho kakudho devaputto bhagavantaṁ etadavoca: ",
    "sn2.18:1.4": "“nandasi, samaṇā”ti? ",
    "sn2.18:1.5": "“Kiṁ laddhā, āvuso”ti? ",
    "sn2.18:1.6": "“Tena hi, samaṇa, socasī”ti? ",
    "sn2.18:1.7": "“Kiṁ jīyittha, āvuso”ti? ",
    "sn2.18:1.8": "“Tena hi, samaṇa, neva nandasi na ca socasī”ti? ",
    "sn2.18:1.9": "“Evamāvuso”ti. ",
    "sn2.18:2.1": "“Kacci tvaṁ anagho bhikkhu, ",
    "sn2.18:2.2": "kacci nandī na vijjati; ",
    "sn2.18:2.3": "Kacci taṁ ekamāsīnaṁ, ",
    "sn2.18:2.4": "aratī nābhikīratī”ti. ",
    "sn2.18:3.1": "“Anagho ve ahaṁ yakkha, ",
    "sn2.18:3.2": "atho nandī na vijjati; ",
    "sn2.18:3.3": "Atho maṁ ekamāsīnaṁ, ",
    "sn2.18:3.4": "aratī nābhikīratī”ti. ",
    "sn2.18:4.1": "“Kathaṁ tvaṁ anagho bhikkhu, ",
    "sn2.18:4.2": "kathaṁ nandī na vijjati; ",
    "sn2.18:4.3": "Kathaṁ taṁ ekamāsīnaṁ, ",
    "sn2.18:4.4": "aratī nābhikīratī”ti. ",
    "sn2.18:5.1": "“Aghajātassa ve nandī, ",
    "sn2.18:5.2": "nandījātassa ve aghaṁ; ",
    "sn2.18:5.3": "Anandī anagho bhikkhu, ",
    "sn2.18:5.4": "evaṁ jānāhi āvuso”ti. ",
    "sn2.18:6.1": "“Cirassaṁ vata passāmi, ",
    "sn2.18:6.2": "brāhmaṇaṁ parinibbutaṁ; ",
    "sn2.18:6.3": "Anandiṁ anaghaṁ bhikkhuṁ, ",
    "sn2.18:6.4": "tiṇṇaṁ loke visattikan”ti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn2.18:0.1": "Linked Discourses 2.18 ",
    "sn2.18:0.2": "2. With Anāthapiṇḍika ",
    "sn2.18:0.3": "With Kakudha ",
    "sn2.18:1.1": "So I have heard. ",
    "sn2.18:1.2": "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāketa in the deer park at the Añjana Wood. ",
    "sn2.18:1.3": "Then, late at night, the glorious godling Kakudha, lighting up the entire Añjana Wood, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, and said to him, ",
    "sn2.18:1.4": "“Do you delight, ascetic?” ",
    "sn2.18:1.5": "“What have I gained, sir?” ",
    "sn2.18:1.6": "“Well then, ascetic, do you sorrow?” ",
    "sn2.18:1.7": "“What have I lost, sir?” ",
    "sn2.18:1.8": "“Well then, ascetic, do you neither delight nor sorrow?” ",
    "sn2.18:1.9": "“Yes, sir.” ",
    "sn2.18:2.1": "“I hope you’re not gloomy, mendicant, ",
    "sn2.18:2.2": "I hope that delight isn’t found in you. ",
    "sn2.18:2.3": "I hope that discontent doesn’t ",
    "sn2.18:2.4": "overwhelm you as you sit alone.” ",
    "sn2.18:3.1": "“I’m genuinely not gloomy, spirit, ",
    "sn2.18:3.2": "and no delight is found in me. ",
    "sn2.18:3.3": "And also discontent doesn’t ",
    "sn2.18:3.4": "overwhelm me as I sit alone.” ",
    "sn2.18:4.1": "“How are you not gloomy, mendicant? ",
    "sn2.18:4.2": "How is delight not found in you? ",
    "sn2.18:4.3": "How does discontent not ",
    "sn2.18:4.4": "overwhelm you as you sit alone?” ",
    "sn2.18:5.1": "“Delight is born from gloom, ",
    "sn2.18:5.2": "gloom is born from delight; ",
    "sn2.18:5.3": "sir, you should know me as ",
    "sn2.18:5.4": "a mendicant free of delight and gloom.” ",
    "sn2.18:6.1": "“After a long time I see ",
    "sn2.18:6.2": "a brahmin fully quenched. ",
    "sn2.18:6.3": "A mendicant free of delight and gloom, ",
    "sn2.18:6.4": "he has crossed over clinging to the world.” "
  },
